## What I Learned:
- DNS is the phonebook of the internet - it translates domain names to IP addresses [citation:5]
- Domain hierarchy: Root → TLD (.com) → Second-Level (example.com) → Subdomain (blog.example.com) [citation:1]
- Maximum domain name length is 253 characters, each label max 63 characters [citation:2]
- Different DNS record types serve different purposes: A (IPv4), AAAA (IPv6), CNAME (alias), MX (email), TXT (text data) [citation:4]
- DNS resolution process: Local cache → Recursive server → Root servers → TLD server → Authoritative server [citation:6]
- TTL (Time To Live) controls how long DNS records are cached

